description._content: Description: Administrator E.B. Sweet-Escott, C.M.G. proceeding to Court House on 9th November, 1903. Location: Seychelles Date: 09 November 1903 Description: 1st Class P.C. Jumeau, Orderly. W.L. Rind (Private Secretary), E.B. Sweet-Escott C.M.G. (Governor of Seychelles), E.B. Sweet-Escott (Assistant Private Secretary.). Location: Seychelles Date: 1900-1929 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/771 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown.
